author: ED GRUVER | Sports Writer
title: L-L Football Week 5: Pioneers, Eagles prepare for potential mud bowl
text:
Marty Heisey | Staff Photographer 
Lampeter-Strasburg's Shane Lawler is one of the playmakers on the Pioneers' offense. 
Cocalico (1-0 Section Two, 2-2 overall)   (0-1 Section Two, 2-2 overall): One of the storylines here is the condition of the Pioneers’ home field following drenching rains and heavy usage. 
Because of the weather forecast the game's starting time has been moved from 7 p.m. to 5 p.m. 
The Eagles’ vaunted Veer ground game is based on execution and quickness; the latter may be hard to come by in muddy conditions. Hunter High, who leads the team in rushing with 429 yards, is averaging 7 yards per haul. DJ Fabiani is at 10 ypc, Trevor Fichthorn 18.6 and Moses Ulysse 10.5. 
L-S counters with a passing game headed by QB Bear Shank and receivers Chad Gaudino and Shane Lawler. More Headlines
